29/04/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- Revisions to the Turkish penal code have been finalised, according to a report Thursday (28 April) by NTV. Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan approved the changes, which he said were in line with media demands concerning limits on freedom of speech. The changes have been forwarded to parliament for debate.
In other news Thursday, the Turkish Defence Industry Undersecretariat sealed a preliminary agreement with the defence firm Roketsan, to build both medium and long range guided anti-tank missiles. The company is the only Turkish producer of missiles. (Anadolu Agency, NTV - 28/04/05) 
